SIMPLE: ably
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ably
<hw>A"bly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In an able manner;
with great ability; <as>as, <ex>ably</ex> done, planned,
said</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-ably</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: -ably
<hw>-a*bly</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A suffix composed of <it>-able</it>
and the adverbial suffix <it>-ly</it>; as, <it>favorably</it>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abnegate</ent>⟦br⟧
